Formats, modes, and colour codings of IEEE 1394 cameras we have used:

Format 0 Mode 0 (4:4:4 YUV8)				API200
Format 0 Mode 1 (4:2:2 YUV8)		A602f,	A602fc,	API200
Format 0 Mode 2 (4:1:1 YUV8)				API200
Format 0 Mode 3 (4:2:2 YUV8)			A602fc,	API200
Format 0 Mode 4 (RGB8)					API200
Format 0 Mode 5 (Mono8)		A301fc,	A602f,	A602fc,	API200
Format 7 Mode 0 Mono8		A301fc,	A602f,	A602fc
Format 7 Mode 0 4:2:2 YUV8			A602fc
Format 7 Mode 0 Mono16			A602f
Format 7 Mode 0 Raw8				A602fc
Format 7 Mode 0 Raw16				A602fc
Format 7 Mode 1 Mono8				A602fc
Format 7 Mode 3 Mono8			A602f

Camera codes:
A301fc	= Basler A301fc		640x480  80fps Bayer colour
A602f	= Basler A602f		640x480 100fps monochrome
A602fc	= Basler A602fc		640x480 100fps Bayer colour
API200	= Pyro 1394 Webcam	640x480  30fps Bayer colour

Average pixel sizes:
Mono8		 8 bits
4:1:1 YUV8	12 bits
4:2:2 YUV8	16 bits
4:4:4 YUV8	24 bits
RGB8		24 bits
Mono16		16 bits
RGB16		48 bits
Mono16 signed	16 bits
RGB16 signed	48 bits
Raw8		 8 bits
Raw16		16 bits
